ken,
right it's asymtotic, not log.
Anyway, I set up a larger training set, but the fitness curve appeared 
to level off far short of close. It is still making improvements, and 
maybe i'll see magic when i get home again, but i'm still dissapointed. 
The chance of adding a node is set to 2%, so i'm crossing my fingers 
that it's just being slow and carefull.
Is there any science to prdicting the size/complexity of a domain before 
starting? My experiment is to find a network that solves a cross 
product. that seems really simple, but it is proving difficult.
chad
